description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced and highly motivated manager with drive and ambition? Do you have proven leadership skills? We are looking for a dynamic individual to provide a full range of business support services to hospital and community based services in the Tiverton and Cullompton cluster area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to ensure the smooth day to day running of a very busy community hospital site at Tiverton. Excellent communication skills and high level IT capabilities are essential for the successful candidate. Developing strong community links and working alongside partners will be key as well as having good negotiation skills. You will need to be able to prioritise efficiently and demonstrate a very high level of organisational ability and skill. Successfully managing projects and health and safety risk management will be a pivotal part of this role. The position is part of an integrated health and social care cluster management team who work flexibly together to achieve the best outcomes for individuals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you believe you have the necessary skills and a forward thinking, creative outlook, please contact Julia Brown, Community Services Manager on 07971 772 191 for an informal discussion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are: &lt;br /&gt; Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt; Fairness&lt;br /&gt; Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt; Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to staff with ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DUE TO THE ANTICIPATED HIGH NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS FOR THIS POST WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE THE VACANCY BEFORE THE CLOSING DATE.&lt;/p&gt;
